‘It’s up to individual players to go away to their clubs and work on these things. Then we should come back for pre-season, hopefully, with all the players tweaking things and returning as better rugby players.

‘Because we do know that we need to step up again for the World Cup. Personally, as a playmaker, I have to take a lot out of this campaign and look at what I can do better. It will come. We will go to the World Cup as a better team.’

As promises go, it’s not quite up there with a dazed David Denton seemingly suggesting that Scotland might contend for the Webb Ellis Trophy half a year down the line. Right now, we would settle for performances that keep the fans at bar’s length from open revolt — and the Mars bars tucked firmly in place between the hip flask and the tartan tammy.

 

